# Shopify Schema Locale Keys — Fashique

## Critical Rule: No Duplicate Top-Level Keys

`en.default.schema.json` MUST have exactly ONE occurrence of each top-level namespace.
Duplicate top-level keys cause **silent overrides** — the LAST one wins and erases all keys in earlier ones.

**Always verify with Node.js (not PowerShell), which matches Shopify's V8 parser:**
```bash
node -e "JSON.parse(require('fs').readFileSync('locales/en.default.schema.json','utf8')); console.log('OK')"
```

---

## Top-Level Namespaces in en.default.schema.json

The file has exactly **6** top-level keys. Never add a 7th or duplicate an existing one:

| Key | Purpose |
|-----|---------|
| `general` | Template/page type names + Theme Settings group names |
| `labels` | ALL setting field labels (theme settings AND section settings shared labels) |
| `info` | ALL helper/description text below settings |
| `options` | ALL select/radio option labels |
| `sections` | Per-section schema translations (`sections.section_name.settings.id.label`) |
| `blocks` | Per-block schema translations |

---

## Theme Settings Keys (settings_schema.json uses these)

When editing `settings_schema.json`, every `t:` key must exist in the corresponding namespace:

### `general.*` — panel group names
`typography`, `layout`, `color_schemes`, `colors`, `advanced`

