## Safe String Values

- Use plain ASCII hyphens `-` instead of em dashes `—` in locale strings to avoid encoding edge cases
- No smart/curly quotes inside string values
- `{{ year }}` (Liquid variable) is allowed in locale strings — e.g. `"Use {{ year }} for the current year."`

---

## Shopify Placeholder SVG Types

Valid types for `placeholder_svg_tag` and `placeholder_type` in `snippets/image.liquid`:

| Type | Valid range |
|------|------------|
| `product-1` … `product-6` | 6 variants |
| `collection-1` … `collection-6` | 6 variants |
| `lifestyle-1` … `lifestyle-2` | **Only 2** — NEVER use lifestyle-3+ |
| `image` | Generic fallback |

When cycling lifestyle placeholders use `modulo: 2 | plus: 1` (gives 1 or 2, never 3+).

---

## Setting Value + t Filter Anti-Pattern

NEVER apply `| t` directly to a setting value — it treats the value as a translation key.

```liquid
{# BAD — if label is "Before", Liquid looks up key "before" which doesn't exist #}
{{ section.settings.before_label | default: 'sections.before_after.before' | t }}

{# GOOD — only apply | t to a known translation key string #}
{%- if section.settings.before_label != blank -%}
  {{ section.settings.before_label | escape }}
{%- else -%}
  {{ 'sections.before_after.before' | t }}
{%- endif -%}
```

Same applies to any `button_label`, `heading`, or other free-text settings that also have `| t` after `| default:`.

---

## Form Tag — No Filter Chains in Parameters

Shopify Liquid form tags do NOT support filter chains in named parameters.

```liquid
{# BAD — | append: inside a form tag parameter causes invalid form type error #}
{%- form 'customer', id: 'email-signup-' | append: section.id -%}

{# GOOD — pre-assign the variable, then reference it #}
{%- assign signup_form_id = 'email-signup-' | append: section.id -%}
{%- form 'customer', id: signup_form_id -%}
```

---

## Adding New Settings

When adding a new setting to `settings_schema.json` with a `t:` reference:
1. Add its `labels.*` key to the **existing** `labels` block in `en.default.schema.json`
2. Add its `info.*` key to the **existing** `info` block (if it has helper text)
3. Add its `options.*` keys to the **existing** `options` block (if it has select options)
4. **Never create a new top-level `labels`/`info`/`options` block** — merge into the existing ones

When adding a new section with a `{% schema %}` block:
1. Add translations under `sections.section_id.name`, `sections.section_id.settings.setting_id.label`, etc.
2. These go inside the **existing** `sections` block
